						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1328, Pārthiva, Jyēshṭha, ba. 7, [Budhavāra],</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1405 May 20 Wednesday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Bukkarāya (II).</hi> It records that, under the orders of <hi rend="bold">Jommaṇṇa-Oḍeya,</hi> a gift was made to the god • • • Nāyanāradēva at <hi rend="bold">Mūgavāḍi</hi> and mentions <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Oḍeya.</hi></p>						

